             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am wife to the prosecutor. I saw the prisoner jump of our window; I called, stop thief! I missed a white apron, and the rest of the things mentioned in the indictment; they were tied up ready in a corner of the window, which is about six feet from the ground; there was light enough to see him,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178602220086"></xptr> I knew him before, he had lodged at our house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17860222-42-person528">
                  THOMAS
                   HERNE
               <interp inst="t17860222-42-person528" type="surname" value="HERNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860222-42-person528" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860222-42-person528" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw the prisoner come out of the window; I attempted to take him, but he was rescued; I am sure the prisoner is the man, he was taken the next day.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I was not near the place; I have neither witnesses nor friends.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17860222-42-verdict233" type="verdictDescription">
